==English==
===Etymology===
Spear sense from [[Old Norse]] ''[[grein]]'' meaning division.  (Reference: [[w:Ray Parkin|Ray Parkin]], ''H. M. Bark Endeavour'', [[w:Miegunyah Press|Miegunyah Press]], second edition 2003, ISBN 0-522-85093-6, page 196.)
===Noun===
'''grains'''
# Plural of [[grain]].
# An iron fish spear with a number of points half-[[barb]]ed inwardly.
#: 1770: ''Served 5 lb of fish per man which was caught by striking with grains'' &mdash; journal of Stephen Forwood (gunner on [[w:HM Bark Endeavour|H.M. Bark ''Endeavour'']]), 4 May 1770, quoted by Parkin (page 195).

